<DOC><DOCNO> AP890816-0266 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-16-89 2021EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f AM-Stanley-Parker     08-16 0141</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Stanley-Parker,0150</SECOND><HEAD>Stanley Buys The Parker Group, A Mass.-Based Fastener-Maker</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Stanley Works, the worldwide toolmaker,announced Wednesday it has completed its purchase of Parker Group, amanufacturer of fastening products.   Parker, based in Northboro, Mass., employs about 400 people atplants in Worcester, Northboro and Southbridge, Mass., and in WestGreenwich, R.I.   The company makes glue guns, stapling products, riveting toolsand soldering tools.   Stanley did not release the terms of the purchase.   ``Parker has developed a leading position in the design,manufacture and sale of fastening products for home improvement andconsumer markets,'' said Gary C. Schuler, president and generalmanager of Stanley-Bostich Inc.   Stanley Group Vice President David M. Hadlow described Parker asa ``good strategic fit'' with other Stanley businesses.   Stanley, based in New Britain, had sales of $1.9 billion in 1988.</TEXT></DOC>